value.0: Svirfneblin or deep gnomes are typically reclusive, suspicious and resentful of intrusion. This one seems grateful for dwarven company and offers to assist in any way with the rothe herd.

Value.value: Our rothe has frenzied! Don't go inside there, the horrible beasts may trample you!

value.0: Rothe are herd animals and one of the primary livestock of humans in Faerûn's northern areas. Deep rothe are usually found in the Underdark. These particular beasts are tended by svirfneblin herders within the dwarven Citadel.

Sewn from some of the finest silks on the island, this cloth is both beautiful, and durable. A set of gloves come with the cloth - a powerful arachnid-magic has been imbued in them to allow the wearer to shoot strands of silk at their foes.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this grade are meager protection, no better than garments made of cloth or even rags.
